// Empty proc; users stick `noop_proc()` inside a func body to force
// constfolder to treat that func as impure (no compile-time fold). It has no
// host side effect, so it stays in core rather than std/sys.til (issue
// #216) -- it is a constfolder escape hatch, not a syscall, and lives here in
// the aggregator because it doesn't belong to any data-type module.
noop_proc := ext_proc() {}
